                            <comment id="13527393" author="miyakawataku" created="Sun, 9 Dec 2012 10:11:33 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;The patch to fix errors in the document &quot;Built In Functions&quot; in trunk/&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13528790" author="cheolsoo" created="Tue, 11 Dec 2012 08:09:28 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Hello Miyakawa,&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Thank you very much for the patch! I have one comment:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;blockquote&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&quot;Syntax&quot; clause of LAST_INDEX_OF function is wrongly written as LAST_INDEX_OF(expression), but the function actually takes three arguments&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/blockquote&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Looking at source code, &lt;tt&gt;LAST_INDEX_OF&lt;/tt&gt; takes only 2 args: string to be searched and substring to search for. Inside the UDF, &lt;tt&gt;string.lastIndexOf(substring)&lt;/tt&gt; is called. In fact, this is inconsistent with &lt;tt&gt;INDEXOF&lt;/tt&gt; that takes the 3rd optional arg (&lt;tt&gt;fromIndex&lt;/tt&gt;).&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Can you please update the patch?&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13533008" author="miyakawataku" created="Sat, 15 Dec 2012 12:18:44 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Thank you for the comment.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;I updated the patch.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13533147" author="cheolsoo" created="Sat, 15 Dec 2012 20:34:03 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Committed to trunk. Thanks Miyakawa!&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
